Using Redux Subspace with redux-loop is pretty straightforward and should require no additional enhancer or middleware configuration. The only difference is that you have to import the namespaced function from redux-subspace-loop instead of using the default one from redux-subspace package. This extends the functionality provided by redux-subspace to also namespace the commands returned by your reducer.
npm install --save redux-subspace-loop

